invoice:
The desired JSON format for representing the extracted data from the invoice should follow the structure outlined below: 

```json 
{
  "Invoice": {
    "Type": "String",
    "InvoiceNumber": "Number",
    "Date": "String (in the following format: MM-DD-YYYY)",
    "Seller": {
      "Name": "String",
      "Address": "String",
      "ContactDetails": {
        "Email": "String",
        "PhoneNumber": "String"
      }
    },
    "Buyer": {
      "Name": "String",
      "Address": "String",
      "ContactDetails": {
        "Email": "String",
        "PhoneNumber": "String"
      }
    },
    "InvoiceDetails": {
        "ProductDetails": {
            "ProductName": "String",
            "Quantity": "Number",
            "Price": "Number"
        },
        "Subtotal": "Number",
        "Tax": "Number",
        "Total": "Number"
    },
    "PaymentDetails": {
      "DueDate": "String (in the following format: MM-DD-YYYY)",
      "PaymentInfo": "String",
      "PaymentStatus": "String"
    }
  }
}
```
This JSON structure captures all key information from an invoice in a clear and organized manner.
